0.4 x + 15 = x
0.4 x
\begin{align} 0.4 x + 15 & = x \\ 0.4 x + 15 - 0.4 x & = x - 0.4 x \\ 15 &= x - 0.4 x \end{align}
 x = 1x
\begin{align} 15 &= x - 0.4 x \\    &= 1x - 0.4x \\    &= x(1-0.4) \\    &= 0.6 x \\ \frac{15}{0.6} & = x \\  x &= \frac{15}{0.6} \\  x &= 25 \end{align}
15=x-0.4x
15=0.6x
x=\frac{15}{0.6}=25
\frac{15}{0.6}=\frac{15}{\frac{6}{10}}=\frac{(15\cdot 10)}{6}=\frac{150}{6}=25
